    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="379"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Hopkins Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President’s Special Assistant</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HHL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>, and
                        Reply by the President</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d379fn1">The relationship of these notes to the Fourth
                        Plenary Meeting appears from internal evidence and from Sherwood, pp.
                        862–864. See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_714">p.
                        714</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Yalta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-07">February 7,
                            1945</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>All of the below refers to <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName>’s
                    opposition to early calling of conference of United Nations.</p>
                <p>There is something behind this talk that we do not know of its basis.</p>
                <p>Perhaps we better to wait till later tonight what is on his mind.</p>
                <p>All this is <del rend="strikethrough">rot</del>! local politics<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d379fn2">This line is in <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>’s handwriting.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I am quite sure now he is thinking about the next election in Britain.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
